<div class="textblock"><p>Information about coding standards, tools, and device support.</p>
<p>Big Fish has established a set of requirements and recommendations for developers to use when they produce games for distribution to the Apple App Store. Games <em>must</em> meet all requirements before they can be accepted and distributed.</p>
<ul>
<li>See the <a class="el" href="checklist.html">Freemium Development Checklist</a> for a summary of the most important Freemium requirements.</li>
<li>See the <a class="el" href="usability.html">Freemium Usability Requirements</a> for more information about Freemium user experience requirements.</li>
<li>See the <a class="el" href="f2p_checklist.html">Free-to-Play Development Checklist</a> for a summary of the most important Free-to-Play requirements.</li>
<li>See the <a class="el" href="f2p_usability.html">Free-to-Play Usability Requirements</a> for more information about Free-to-Play user experience requirements.</li>
</ul>
<h1><a class="anchor" id="dev_tools"></a>
Development Tools</h1>
<p>Use the following development tools and libraries to create applications for Big Fish:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Xcode:</b> Xcode is the exclusive development platform for Big Fish iOS: Xcode versions 5.0 and up (Apple requirement as of Feb. 1, 2014), using .xcodeproj files as opposed to Xcode workspaces.</li>
<li><b>SVN:</b> Big Fish provides an external SVN repository for build submissions.</li>
<li><b>JIRA:</b> Big Fish uses <a href=" http://extmon.bigfishgames.com:8080/secure/Dashboard.jspa" class="el" target="_blank">JIRA</a> to track bugs. You <em>must</em> update the bug database before you submit changes for any build.</li>
<li><b>Big Fish iOS Software Development Kit (Big Fish iOS SDK):</b> The SDK contains the code to implement the game features that are unique to Big Fish.</li>
</ul>
<dl class="section note"><dt>Note</dt><dd>If you use additional development tools and libraries, you <em>must</em> include them in build submissions to Big Fish.</dd></dl>
<p><b>Additional resources:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>For more information about Xcode, see Apple’s <a href="http://developer.apple.com/technologies/tools/" class="el" target="_blank">Xcode documentation</a>.</li>
<li>To validate your JSON code, an online JSON validator tool is available at <a href="http://jsonlint.com" class="el" target="_blank">JSONLint</a>.</li>
<li>For more information about SVN and JIRA requirements, see <a class="el" href="production.html#Build_requirements">Build Requirements</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="bfg_iOS_kit"></a>
Big Fish iOS Software Development Kit (Big Fish iOS SDK)</h2>
<p>The Big Fish iOS SDK contains a framework for the major Big Fish components that you can quickly add to your game project. These components include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Ad integration</li>
<li>Promotional features, such as the Game Discovery Network (GDN) and the iSplash! newsletter.</li>
<li>Branding</li>
<li>Rating</li>
<li>Reporting</li>
<li>In-game purchase</li>
<li>Login</li>
</ul>
<p>The Big Fish iOS SDK also includes an example code project and documentation.</p>
<p>Big Fish adds an external link from the trunk branch of the external SVN repository for your title, to the current version of the Big Fish iOS SDK. When you check out code from the trunk branch of your repository, the build team adds a folder containing the latest version of the Big Fish iOS SDK.</p>
<ul>
<li>For more information about the framework, see <a class="el" href="reference_class.html">Classes and Components</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="thirdPartyTools"></a>
Third-party tools and libraries</h2>
<p>Third-party tools and libraries that you use to build your game project <em>must</em> meet the following requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Submit tools with the build:</b> You <em>must</em> submit all third-party tools required for a build with the build. Big Fish will not accept links to tools or requests to download a tool or library.</li>
<li><b>Compatible with Mac OS:</b> All tools that you use to build a game target <em>must</em> run on Mac OS. Big Fish will <em>not</em> accept builds that use tools that require Microsoft Windows.</li>
</ul>
 
    <div style=color:red><blockquote><b>Important:</b> Big Fish will reject builds that do not fulfill the above requirements. Rejected builds are <b>not</b> eligible for milestone payments.</blockquote></div>
<ul>
<li><b>Scripts:</b> If a tool is required to build your project in Xcode, include a script that runs the tool. Do not include scripts that add language folders.</li>
<li><b>Installation instructions:</b> If a tool requires installation, say so in your build notes and include installation instructions. Documentation provided along with the tool will suffice. If possible, provide a script to install the tool. If a tool changes during production, you <em>must</em> document the changes in your build notes.</li>
<li><b>Pre-compiled source code:</b> The complete pre-compiled source code <em>must</em> be included in your project.</li>
<li><b>Open standards:</b> All libraries <em>must</em> comply with open standards, and support a free license, unless Big Fish already has a paid license.</li>
<li><b>Library source code:</b> All libraries <em>must</em> be included as source, unless Big Fish approves an exception.</li>
<li><b>Add libraries to the project:</b> All libraries <em>must</em> be included as part of the Xcode project, either as a separate target, or directly within the game project.</li>
<li><b>No converted data:</b> Do <em>not</em> provide executables or encrypted data.</li>
<li><b>No private APIs:</b> Apple does <em>not</em> allow the use of private APIs. Do <em>not</em> use private APIs in your code.</li>
<li><b>Apple requirements:</b> All libraries <em>must</em> comply with all of <a href="http://developer.apple.com/appstore/resources/approval/guidelines.html" class="el" target="_blank">Apple’s requirements</a> for third-party libraries.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="devResourcesFtpSite"></a>
Developer Resources FTP Site</h2>
<p>Big Fish has set up a <a href="ftp://ftp.bigfishgames.com/Developer_Resources/iOS/" class="el" target="_blank">Developer Resources FTP Site</a>, which contains the Generic Locs and the iTeamTestPass zip files. For login access, contact your Big Fish Producer.</p>
<h1><a class="anchor" id="codingStandards"></a>
Coding Standards</h1>
<p>To facilitate game development among multiple developers and other people in the production process who are not primarily developers, you <em>must</em> use consistent coding standards.</p>
<p>The Big Fish producers have created a set of recommended coding standards. These standards apply to languages derived from C, including Objective C, C, and C++.</p>
<p>Most developers use one of these languages. If you use another language, these standards might not apply.</p>
<ul>
<li>Use spaces, not tabs, for indentation. Use four (4) spaces for each level of indentation.</li>
<li>Place braces on their own lines.</li>
<li>Use braces in case statements, and add one break statement after the case statement.</li>
<li>Limit each line to one statement.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you use an existing set of consistent coding standards that vary from these recommendations, Big Fish does not require that you change your standards to match the recommendations. <b><em>However, Big Fish does require four (4) spaces for each level of indentation.</em></b></p>
<h1><a class="anchor" id="deviceSWsupport"></a>
Device and Software Support</h1>
<p>Big Fish requires all new games to run on iOS 5.0 or later versions and to support the armv7 architecture.</p>
<p>The game <em>must</em> detect the device type automatically and provide features based on the detected device type. </p>
